<p class="eyebrow"><a href="/docs/api/">API reference</a> / <a href="/docs/api/v2.1/">v2.1</a> / Credentials</p>
<h1>API credentials.</h1>
<p class="lede">Every VoiceTel account is provisioned with a single API key that authorizes every REST endpoint. Retrieve it from the portal, then attach it to each request using either an <code>Authorization</code> header or an <code>apikey</code> field in the JSON body.</p>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>API key</h2>
	<p>Each account automatically receives a unique API key derived from a cryptographic hash-based message authentication code (HMAC). The key is account-scoped — there is no separate sandbox key, and the same key authorizes every REST endpoint on the platform.</p>
	<p>Retrieve your API key at:</p>
	<p><a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://api.voicetel.com/apikey/" rel="external">api.voicetel.com/apikey</a></p>
	<p>The portal returns the key to the authenticated session. Treat it like a password: anyone holding the key can act on the account.</p>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Authentication</h2>
	<p>Two interchangeable schemes are supported. Pick whichever fits your client:</p>

	<h3>Bearer header (recommended)</h3>
	<p>RFC&nbsp;6750 bearer token. The standard <code>Authorization</code> header keeps secrets out of request bodies, query strings, and access logs that capture URLs but not headers.</p>
	<pre class="code-block"><code>curl -X POST 'https://api.voicetel.com/v2.1/info/cnam' \
  -H 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{ "cid": 2015551234 }'</code></pre>

	<h3>JSON payload (v2.1 only)</h3>
	<p>For clients that cannot set custom request headers, v2.1 also accepts the API key as an <code>apikey</code> field on the JSON request body. Functionally equivalent on v2.1; choose only when the Bearer header is impractical.</p>
	<pre class="code-block"><code>curl -X POST 'https://api.voicetel.com/v2.1/info/cnam' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{
    "apikey": "YOUR_API_KEY",
    "cid": 2015551234
  }'</code></pre>

	<p>If both are present, the header takes precedence.</p>
	<p><strong>Note:</strong> the JSON-payload form is removed in <a href="/docs/api/v2.2/credentials/">v2.2</a>. Migrate any client that depends on it to the <code>Authorization</code> header before switching to the v2.2 base URL.</p>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Rotating the key</h2>
	<p>API key rotation is performed from the portal. After rotation the previous key is invalidated immediately; deployed integrations must be updated to the new key before the change is committed.</p>
	<p>For rotation help on a live integration, contact engineering before rotating so we can coordinate the cutover.</p>
	<p><a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/contact/">Contact us</a></p>
</section>

